    "John Trapp": "Ver. 14,\nVer. 14,\n14. Bitter with hard bondage. ] Did we but live a while, saith one, { a } in Turkey, Persia, yea, or but in France, a dram of that liberty we yet enjoy would be as precious to us as a drop of cold water would have been to the rich man in hell, when he was so grievously tormented in those flames. { a } Mercer.\nVer.\n14. Bitter with hard bondage.] Did we but live a while, saith one, {a} in Turkey, Persia, yea, or but in France, a dram of that liberty we yet enjoy would be as precious to us as a drop of cold water would have been to the rich man in hell, when he was so grievously tormented in those flames. {a} Mercer.\nVer.",
